# C Assembler Project

## Overview
This project implements a two-pass assembler in C, simulating the compilation process of assembly code into machine code.

## Features
- Two-pass assembly process (first pass and second pass)
- Lexical and syntactic parsing of assembly instructions
- Symbol table construction and management
- Memory allocation and address resolution
- Error detection and handling
- Modular and maintainable code design

## Technologies
- C programming language
- Linux environment
- Git for version control

## Project Structure
- `main.c` – main program flow
- `first_pass.c` – first pass logic
- `second_pass.c` – second pass logic
- `symbol_table.c` – symbol management
- Additional helper files as needed

## How to Run
1. Compile the project:
make
or:
gcc *.c -o assembler
2. Run the assembler:
./assembler input_file.as

## Notes
This project was developed as part of an academic course in systems programming and focuses on low-level programming concepts and efficient memory handling.








